    "recap_headline": "Princeton University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SPARTANBURG, S.C. -\nPrinceton baseball swept\u00a0their Saturday doubleheader against the Wofford Terriers on Saturday.\nPrinceton 3, Wofford 0\nPrinceton opened up scoring at the top of the fifth inning with a three spot.\nJake Koonin\nput up the first run on the board with an RBI, sending\nBennett Crerar\nacross the plate.\nBrady Kaufman\nfollowed with an run-producing single with\nTomas Cernius\ncoming around to score.\nIsaac Lamson\nput up the final run with an RBI groundout.\nJustin Kim\nhad a tremendous seven-inning outing, allowing just three hits and earning two strikeouts.\nPrinceton 6, Wofford 5\nIn the third inning, Princeton opened up the scoring with Crerar reaching first base on an error by Wofford's defense, allowing\nJake Kernodle\nto cross the plate, taking the 1-0 lead.\nWofford responded, putting up five runs continued to put up five runs between the fifth and sixth innings.\nThe Tigers answered back in the seventh inning with RBI singles from\nGrant Werdesheim\nand Crerar.\nCernius's RBI knock got the Tigers within one before\nWill Robbins\nfollowed with a RBI hit to tie the game at 5-all. A Wofford error put Princeton ahead in the 11th.\nWofford put a runner on third base with two outs, but\nKasey Gilman\ngot a strikeout to end the contest and earn the save.\nLiam Kinneen\nstarted on the mound for the Tigers, striking out six over five innings.\nThe Tigers play their final game of the Spring Break trip Sunday against Wofford with first pitch scheduled for 1 p.m."
